  "prompt": "Why does my face clear up during my period?",
  "response": "Hormonal changes during your menstrual cycle can affect your skin in different ways. Some women experience clearer skin during their period due to:\n\n1. Decreased androgen levels\n- Androgens (male hormones) can increase oil production\n- During menstruation, androgen levels drop, potentially reducing acne\n\n2. Lower progesterone levels\n- High progesterone can contribute to breakouts\n- Progesterone levels decrease during menstruation\n\n3. Reduced inflammation\n- Hormonal shifts can decrease overall skin inflammation\n\nHowever, skin responses vary among individuals. Some women might experience breakouts instead of clearer skin. Factors like:\n- Genetics\n- Stress\n- Diet\n- Skincare routine\n\ncan also influence skin condition during your menstrual cycle.\n\nIf you have persistent skin concerns, consulting a dermatologist can provide personalized insights.",
